Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.53,0:00:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.23,0:00:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.06,0:00:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What was "the usual"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.67,0:00:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When are you going to\Nremember it Robby?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.17,0:00:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A hamburger, double cheese, extra\Nketchup, and thick slices of tomato.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.11,0:00:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll kill you if you\Nput pickles in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.88,0:00:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I supposed to\Nremember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.52,0:00:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That Chinese or Vietnamese guy\Nis sniffing you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.70,0:00:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been coming here often.\NHe was asking who you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.67,0:00:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not Chinese\Nor Vietnamese.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.24,0:01:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.78,0:01:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.85,0:01:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's a neurosurgeon.\NAnd a brilliant one at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.32,0:01:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.76,0:01:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.30,0:01:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And you used to be engaged to\Nthe hospital director's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.54,0:01:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you planning\Nto do with Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.31,0:01:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.71,0:01:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being too\Nfamiliar with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.51,0:01:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When are you going to stop\Nthinking of her as your fiancé?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.01,0:01:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,From what I hear, you're no\Nlonger a doctor, but a fugitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.19,0:01:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just get in there and get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.99,0:01:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you behave you might\Nget out one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.06,0:01:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let Eva go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.26,0:01:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let her go?\NI haven't been confining her at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.97,0:01:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, she's been going\Nto parties every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me. ..see Eva.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.47,0:02:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let you see her"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.98,0:02:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.02,0:02:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mess up my shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.59,0:02:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hang around\Nhere anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.02,0:02:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.59,0:02:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,E-Eva...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.40,0:02:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.76,0:03:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw Kenzo?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.76,0:04:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, two days ago.\NThought I'd let you know, just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.60,0:04:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.04,0:04:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't hit him, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.68,0:04:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No. I wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.08,0:04:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.38,0:04:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Did you have\Nenough of today's party?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.79,0:04:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,For today.\NOr rather, the party is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.29,0:04:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.30,0:04:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work, Eva.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.14,0:04:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How about dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.38,0:04:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:05:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So you dropped her off with\Nyour client at the restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.82,0:05:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're eating\Ndinner here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.52,0:05:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The hamburgers here\Nare way better
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.62,0:05:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,than the food at those parties\Nand expensive restaurants.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.86,0:05:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure whether you're\Npraising me or insulting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.38,0:05:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure are persistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.61,0:05:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to\Nget hurt again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.59,0:05:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What part of "get lost"\Ndon't you underst–
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.82,0:05:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move either,\NMr. Manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.96,0:05:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you move, I'll shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.53,0:05:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What a dangerous doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.20,0:05:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Who hired you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.23,0:05:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that your immediate boss\Nis The Baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But the person who ordered you\Nto escort Eva
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.14,0:05:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is someone further up\Nin the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.58,0:06:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Who gave you your orders?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.71,0:06:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.91,0:06:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But. ..I know his face.\NHe wears glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.52,0:06:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A man with glasses?\NWhat is he making Eva do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, didn't I?\NHe's just making her go to parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.53,0:06:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She drinks, eats, and leaves.\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.66,0:06:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't just be ! Eva should have\Nbeen ordered to perform a specific task!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.54,0:06:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.78,0:06:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, today...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Today...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.48,0:06:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.71,0:06:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She pointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.58,0:06:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Pointed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.59,0:06:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To a young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A young man...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.13,0:06:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a young blond man\Nwith a pretty face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That was it though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.93,0:06:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Eva right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.74,0:07:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She's having dinner with my boss,\Nthe man with the glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.67,0:07:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Where?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.24,0:07:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me quickly!\NWhere are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.41,0:07:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva's job is probably over!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.48,0:07:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Once this job is over,\NI'll probably be killed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.95,0:07:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The party is over.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Eva?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.86,0:07:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.62,0:07:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I dropped her off at her hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.43,0:08:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.27,0:08:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No. I try not to\Ncarry one around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.34,0:08:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.91,0:08:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.92,0:08:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That party was the same\Nas it always was.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.16,0:08:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The smell of alcohol,\Nthe smell of perfume,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.73,0:08:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}meaningless laughter...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.43,0:08:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was the same as always.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.13,0:08:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Except for that one moment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.84,0:08:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The moment when Eva\Npointed at a young man...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.01,0:08:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When she did,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.28,0:08:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the man with glasses appeared with\Nanother well-dressed young man.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.59,0:09:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then, those two young men\Nshook hands.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.96,0:09:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I didn't notice it at the time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.29,0:09:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It seems that that's when\NEva's job was over.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.75,0:09:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that you would be\Nthe one to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.49,0:09:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Go right ahead.\NThe drinks are settling in nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.89,0:09:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no lasting regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.80,0:09:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.\NYou can't shoot me in this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.24,0:09:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You told me before that\Nyou shot your girlfriend
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.74,0:09:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and found yourself in\Na pool of blood, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.44,0:09:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Take me outside\Nand shoot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:10:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't, you'll have to pay\Nfor messing up the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.69,0:10:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. I do have one regret...\None last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.89,0:10:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But. ..it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.06,0:10:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what I did today?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.47,0:10:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw me pointing,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.14,0:10:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably did\Nsomething terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.97,0:10:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I let a terrible person and\Na demon come together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.94,0:10:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I bring Mephistopheles\Nand Faust together?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.08,0:10:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.16,0:10:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like I don't need to\Ngo to parties anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.33,0:10:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But I still have my invitation\Nto the next party.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.50,0:10:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want, you can go and confirm\Nwhat I've done after you shoot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.84,0:11:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then. .. Finish me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.71,0:11:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.88,0:11:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Run away with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.39,0:11:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to be getting\Nthe wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.23,0:11:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Run away with you?\NYou're kidding, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.96,0:11:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When did we\Nbecome so friendly?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.54,0:11:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't kill people anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.57,0:11:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't kill people? Are you saying\Nthat you could kill a devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.14,0:11:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.85,0:11:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That suit and necktie\NI bought for you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.62,0:11:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,were the same as the ones\Nthat Kenzo used to wear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.48,0:11:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand? I was just turning you\Ninto Kenzo Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.22,0:11:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.00,0:11:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill me quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.80,0:11:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.17,0:12:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill me...quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.24,0:12:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't kill me quickly...\Nyou'll be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.10,0:12:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill a devil, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.27,0:12:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hey, wake up!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.54,0:12:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's all right.\NI'm just sobering up a bit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.38,0:12:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No! You'll die\Nif you sleep here!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.52,0:12:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's all right.\NJust leave me here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.30,0:13:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You look depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.71,0:13:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm always depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.74,0:13:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Did someone come\Nlooking for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.28,0:13:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no one. But the Japanese man\Nfrom yesterday left this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.45,0:14:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Helbrau Hotel, room 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.62,0:14:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He said to call him\Nif something happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you have?\NThe usual?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.23,0:14:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Not now. I won't feel like doing anything\Nif I fill myself with your crappy burgers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.74,0:14:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.24,0:14:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A party.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.01,0:14:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How strange. I can go anywhere\Nif I have a necktie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.82,0:14:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,With just this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.66,0:14:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.63,0:14:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So is he a devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.03,0:14:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He shook hands\Nwith so many people.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So many that his hands\Nwere probably swollen.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.34,0:14:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then he left the party.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.55,0:15:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Floor six, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But which room is his?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.19,0:15:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.20,0:15:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right this way.\NHave a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.60,0:15:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hesitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.94,0:15:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to meet him too,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.11,0:16:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.21,0:16:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm waiting for him as well.\NHe'll be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.28,0:16:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Before he comes,\Nlet's talk about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.59,0:16:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.95,0:16:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.99,0:16:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about\Nthe end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.96,0:16:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The young man happily talked.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.57,0:16:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Like a child who was\Ntelling his parents{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.57,0:16:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}about something fun that\Nhappened at school that day.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.57,0:16:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's how he talked to me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.98,0:16:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The end of the world?\NThe silly talk of a fanatical young man.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.78,0:16:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's what I thought\Nat the time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.82,0:16:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\NInteresting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.29,0:16:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you amused, Martin?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.56,0:16:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.00,0:17:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah,\Nlet's talk about you next.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.24,0:17:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been with The Baby for\Nalmost three years, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.11,0:17:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You looked me up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.51,0:17:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Before that,\Nyou were in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.01,0:17:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight years...\NThat must have been terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.21,0:17:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You got out on good behavior, right?\NYou sure got out quickly, for a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.15,0:17:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it fun living\Nwith your girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.96,0:17:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The girlfriend you shot.\NHer name was.. .Edda.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.60,0:17:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's in pretty bad taste, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.46,0:17:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She was quite\Nthe drug addict wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.27,0:17:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You desperately tried\Nto get her clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.74,0:17:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty difficult to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.81,0:17:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it love?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.44,0:17:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to get hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.85,0:17:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She recovered. She made dinner and\Nwaited for you to return home each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Your happy life\Ntogether began.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.25,0:17:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "do you want\Nto get punched?"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But that night...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.89,0:17:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When you returned to your room,\Nyou saw something outrageous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.10,0:18:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She was with her ex-boyfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.93,0:18:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She had done drugs again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.37,0:18:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Though disoriented, she saw you and\Nsaid over and over again, "I'm sorry."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.88,0:18:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.42,0:18:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm sorry."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.19,0:18:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But you shot her along\Nwith that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.19,0:18:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the story at your trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.06,0:18:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.86,0:18:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She killed herself, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.43,0:18:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Your lawyer determined\Nthat she killed herself
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.74,0:18:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because there were traces\Nof gunpowder on her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.51,0:18:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But you stuck to the story\Nthat you shot her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.91,0:18:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She asked you to kill her,\Ndidn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.02,0:18:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I right?!\NI'm right, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.55,0:19:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought so.\NYou weren't the one who shot her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.03,0:19:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, she told you\Nto shoot her, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.26,0:19:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shoot me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.30,0:19:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't look at me like that!\NKill me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.64,0:19:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kill me!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.41,0:19:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Martin!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I didn't do it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.32,0:19:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She shot herself!\NIt wasn't me!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.87,0:19:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Right? It wasn't me, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.41,0:19:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought so. Amazing.\NI'm right, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.21,0:19:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.41,0:20:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You left her behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.68,0:20:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you\Ngranted her wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.49,0:20:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.45,0:20:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what about your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.59,0:20:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother froze to death\Nwhen you were ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time,\Nyou left your mother behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.50,0:20:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I right again?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.57,0:20:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing, amazing. I'm surprised.\NI really got it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.44,0:20:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyday, you'd carry\Nyour alcoholic mother home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.08,0:20:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.31,0:20:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother would always tell you\Nto leave her where she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.62,0:20:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, you'd carry her home\Nevery day. But that night...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.09,0:20:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, you can't sleep here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.96,0:20:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's all right. It's all right.\NLeave me right here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.64,0:20:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wake up!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.69,0:21:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You left her there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.79,0:21:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?\NYou left your mother there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.03,0:21:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, you were informed\Nthat your mother had frozen to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.70,0:21:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But at that time,\Nyou thought that you weren't at fault
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.27,0:21:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you left her there\Nbecause she told you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.68,0:21:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NYou're not at fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.34,0:21:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother and your drug-addicted\Ngirlfriend both wanted to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.92,0:21:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You were letting people who\Nwanted to die, do what they wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.39,0:21:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not wrong.\NYou're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.29,0:21:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You released them\Nfrom the pain of living.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.56,0:21:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva also wants to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.48,0:22:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was at that moment...\Nthe devil arrived.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.99,0:22:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I passed by him,\Ncareful not to look.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.96,0:22:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Like a child, I repeated to myself,\N"Don't look, don't look. Don't dare look."{\i0}
